A man killed in a suspected hit-and-run crash near Hassocks has been named by police. Tony Barrow, 64, was found dead by the side of a road at Clayton Hill in the early hours of 18 May. He was hit by a vehicle that did not stop after colliding with him, Sussex Police said. A 59-year-old man from Hove was arrested on suspicion of causing death by careless driving and failing to stop after a road accident. He has now been released on police bail. People who were driving in the area, particularly between 00:15 and 00:40 BST, have been asked to contact the police with information.  Follow BBC South East on Facebook, on Twitter, and on Instagram. Send your story ideas to southeasttoday@bbc.co.uk.
